libdrm-cursor (1.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix min-interval overflow when setting max fps > 1000
  * Fix compile warning
  * Fix error out when monitor disconnected
  * Support using linear when AFBC also supported
  * Prefer linear by default
  * Fix more compile warnings

 -- Jeffy Chen <jeffy.chen@rock-chips.com>  Wed, 01 Dec 2021 15:48:26 +0800

libdrm-cursor (1.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Only verify the first cursor set request
  * Update cursor offsets before handling any requests
  * debian: Allow error in prerm stage

 -- Jeffy Chen <jeffy.chen@rock-chips.com>  Thu, 09 Sep 2021 11:41:45 +0800

libdrm-cursor (1.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Update CRTC status when setting cursor
  * Prefer non-modifier gbm API when not using modifier
  * Avoid moving cursor in error state
  * Support edge pre-moving
  * Use the same log APIs for egl
  * Fix invalid cursor size in first commit

 -- Jeffy Chen <jeffy.chen@rock-chips.com>  Wed, 04 Aug 2021 15:27:16 +0800

libdrm-cursor (1.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cache CRTC size
  * Rework atomic API flow
  * Add timestamp in drm logs
  * Support limiting cursor FPS
  * Force legacy drm API for cursor planes
  * Use legacy drm API when kernel supports async commit
  * Support disabling atomic drm API

